ss function of the Hyades\ncontinues to be shallow below 0.15 $M_\\odot$ indicating that the Hyades have\nprobably lost their lowest mass members by means of dynamical evolution. We\nconclude that the Hyades core represents the `VLM/BD desert' and that most of\nthe substeller objects may have already left the volume of the cluster.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 12 Jan 2018 20:19:19 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-03-21"}
